content:
The Digital Insurance Platform is built on top of Salesforce and provides components for policy administration, benefit administration, claims, and billing systems used by the insurance industry vertical.

For details about the data model that underlies Insurance, see Insurance and Financial Services Data Model.

An org is a Salesforce deployment with a defined set of licensed users. Your org includes all your data and applications, and it is separate from all other orgs.

Insurance guardrails help you get the most out of Insurance. Guidelines define best practice recommendations to optimize your adoption of the Insurance product for best performance. Limits are boundaries beyond which features are unavailable or performance is throttled.

The Digital Insurance Platform helps agents, brokers, and carriers improve efficiency, drive growth, and create deeper policyholder relationships. Explore examples of fully built applications, learn what's included, setup recommendations, and get ready for implementation.

Learning journeys guide you to the best learning content to get skilled up and ready to succeed in your implementation projects.
title: Digital Insurance Platform Overview
